==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[acumen]], ''[[sharp]] [[point]]''

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] {{IPA|/ˈæk.jə.mən/}}.  Obsolete {{IPA|/ə.kjuˈmən/}}

===Noun===
'''acumen'''
# Quickness of perception or discernment; penetration of mind; the faculty of nice discrimination.

====Quotations====
<blockquote>
<p>No, no, my dear Watson!  With all respect for your natural
acumen, I do not think that you are quite a match for the worthy
doctor. 
<br />[[w:Arthur Conan Doyle|Sir Arthur Conan Doyle]] in ''[[wikisource:The Adventure of the Missing Three-Quarter|The Adventure of the Missing Three-Quarter]]''</p></blockquote>

====Synonyms====
*[[Sharpness]]; [[sagacity]]; [[keenness]]; [[shrewdness]]; [[acuteness]].

